 Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":45,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":80,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Peter de Bekering was born in Beckering, Lincolnshire, England as the son of Robert de Tirington and Miss FitzMathew. He had at least 1 son with Agnes Lincoln."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1198–Male":"1198–Surnud","1206":"1206","1216":"1216","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","Abt 1198":"umbes 1198","1198":"1198","1207":"1207","Beckering, Lincolnshire, England":"Beckering, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1198–Male":"1198–Kuollut","1206":"1206","1216":"1216","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","Abt 1198":"noin 1198","1198":"1198","1207":"1207","Beckering, Lincolnshire, England":"Beckering, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1198–Male":"1198–Décé